        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 4:19PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 419 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Rutherfordton, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
South Mountains State Park, Shingle Hollow, Green Hill, Thermal City,
Sunshine, Union Mills, Dysartsville, and Fero.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
